In article <22g2nnINNoo7@iskut.ucs.ubc.ca> unruh@physics.ubc.ca (William Unruh) writes:
>>        cat /dev/audio | compress - | des private_key  > foo
>
>
>Why the compress step- I suspect it would introduce more information
>into the stream rather than less.

You do the compress because /dev/audio (especially with no mike plugged in)
produces a very low entropy output (only the LSB changing, usually).

This is recommended only with no mike plugged in, so that what you're
sampling is noise in the circuitry.

